    <body>
        <head><num xml:lang="en">2273</num>. <term xml:lang="ta">toyyil eṉṉum peyar</term></head>
        <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="Tiv11.372">
          <l>uḻavu nīri leḻuvatōr putalum</l>
          <l>kuḻaivu makiḻcciyu maḻaku meṉṟivai</l>
          <l>tuyaruṅ kūṟun toyyiṟ kiḷavi.<anchor xml:id="Tiv2273-note1"/></l>
          <trailer>(372)</trailer>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
            <l>The word <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">toyyil</foreign> refers to:</l>
            <l rend="indent">ploughing, water spinach (i.e. a shrub growing in water),</l>
            <l rend="indent">these — tenderness, delight, &amp; beauty —,</l>
            <l rend="indent">and grief.</l>
        </lg>
        </div>

        <head><num xml:lang="en">2274</num>. <term xml:lang="ta">arākam eṉṉum peyar</term></head>
        <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="Tiv11.373">
          <l>kītamu niṟamuñ cenniṟak keḻuvu</l>
          <l>mācaiyu muṭukiyalu marāka meṉappaṭum.<anchor xml:id="Tiv2274-note1"/></l>
          <trailer>(373)</trailer>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
            <l><foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">Arākam</foreign> is said to be:</l>
            <l rend="indent">a song, a colour, having a red colour,</l>
            <l rend="indent">desire, or a <foreign>muṭukiyal</foreign> verse.</l>
        </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
