<note xml:lang="en" target="#Tiv2274-note1">
The 2004 <title xml:lang="ta">Cānti Cātaṉa</title> edition identifies this headword as <foreign xml:lang="ta">irākam</foreign> (<ref target="https://archive.org/details/dli.jZY9lup2kZl6TuXGlZQdjZp7kZUy.TVA_BOK_0002448/page/102/mode/1up">11.247</ref>), although that variant is not reported in the critical edition. Another possibility is <foreign xml:lang="ta">āram</foreign> (<abbr corresp="#BnF239"/>), since both <foreign xml:lang="ta">toyyil</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">āram</foreign> are words for <q>sandal paste</q>.
</note>
